# Devices udev's automounter (/etc/udev/scripts/mount.sh) must never touch.
# On this board mmcblk0 is eMMC and mmcblk1 is the SD card; neither is
# removable media. Both hold the RAUC A/B slots, which must stay unmounted so
# `rauc install` can write to the inactive slot, and /data, which is mounted
# by rauc-setup-env.service instead. USB storage (/dev/sd*) is unaffected and
# still automounts.
/dev/mmcblk
